The paper introduces a neural network architecture for planning under partial observability, which is a common problem in robotics and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also focuses on robotic tasks in simulation, which suggests cs.RO (Robotics) as another likely sub-category. The QMDP-net is a recurrent policy network that uses end-to-end learning, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The QMDP-net is also fully differentiable and allows for transfer learning, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses simulations of robotic tasks, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
